radiographic_examinations.findings: No acute intracranial hemorrhage, edema, mass effect, or vascular territorial infarct. Normal size and morphology of ventricles and sulci. Preserved gray-white matter differentiation. Calcifications in the cavernous carotid and vertebral arteries. Rightward deviation of the nasal septum, without associated bony spur. Pneumatized left middle turbinate. Well aerated paranasal sinuses. Clear middle ear cavities and mastoid air cells. Symmetric globes, optic nerves, and extraocular muscles. Glaucoma shunt noted on the left.
